<subSubSection id="C32ADAB5FFE10F45F782F454C637F2E4" pageId="19" pageNumber="202" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8F893EFFE10F45F782F454C637F2E4" blockId="19.[2066,2660,2859,3281]" lastBlockId="19.[1454,2660,3292,3477]" pageId="19" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis id="B944552CFFE10F45F782F454C573F3AF" bold="true" box="[2066,2310,3051,3084]" pageId="19" pageNumber="202">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head—body 97-124 mm, tail 52-72 mm, hindfoot 18-20 mm. No specific data are available for ear length or body weight. Bocage’s Fat Mouse is medium-sized but large for a species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C30F2BDFFE10F45F677F336C62BF309" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1846" box="[2535,2654,3209,3242]" class="Mammalia" family="Nesomyidae" genus="Steatomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="202" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Steatomys</taxonomicName>
. Tail is noticeable short and hairy, darker above than below. Fur is reddish brown dorsally, clearly demarcated from pure white belly. Chin, throat, and upper chest are white. Ears are relatively large and rounded. Limbs are white, with four digits on forefoot and five digits on hindfoot. It has eight nipples.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32ADAB5FFE10F45FA3EF2EDC5A7F2CC" box="[1454,2514,3410,3439]" pageId="19" pageNumber="202" type="biology_ecology">
